programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 1
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 1: IIrun - Arrate. Eibar (171km)'. Starting in Irún, on the French/Spanish border, the race travels to a steep summit finish near Sanctuary of Arrate. The route adds up to 171 kilometres.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 2
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 2: Pamplona - Lekunberri (151km)'. Riders climb the bumpy road to the Sanctuary of San Miguel de Aralar, then they fly down 17 km of smooth asphalt into Lekunberri.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 3
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 3: La Laguna Negra - Vinuesa (163.8km)'. The 3rd stage serves the second uphill finish on La Vuelta, although the final climb is not the hardest climb in the world, it's a long 18 kilometres.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 4
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 4: Garray. Numancia - Ejea de los Caballeros (190km)'. Stage 4 travels from Garray to Ejea de los Caballeros. A bunch sprint is the most likely scenario.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 5
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 5: Huesca - Sabinanigo (182.5km)'. The 5th stage plays out in the foothills of the Pyrenees. Following a rolling route for 115 km the last 70 km are quite demanding.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 6
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 6: Biescas - Sallent de Gállego (146.4km)'. The race from Biescas to the Tourmalet could become the stuff of legends.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 7
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 7: Vitoria-Gasteiz - Villanueva de Valdegovia (160.4km)'. At 160.4 kilometres, the 7th stage of La Vuelta is a challenging race through the hills between Vitoria Gasteiz and Valdegovia.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 8
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 8: Logrono Alto de Moncalvillo (164.5km)'. Wine region La Rioja hosts a race from Logroño to an uphill finish at the Moncalvillo. While featuring one intermediate climb, the race amounts to 164.5 km.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 9
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 9: Castrillo del Val - Aguilar de Campoo (163.6km)'. At 163.6 kilometres, the race from Castrillo de Val to Aguilar de Campoo should come down to a sprint finish.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 10
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 10: Castro Urdiales - Suances (187.4km)'. At 187.4 kilometres, stage 10 on La Vuelta travels on flat to bumpy roads close to the Bay of Biscay. The race runs from Castro Urdiales to Suances.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 11
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 11: Villaviciosa - Alto de La Farrapona (170.2km)'. Stage 11 runs from Villaviciosa to a summit finish at La Farrapona, while three huge and one small intermediate climbs will add to the fatigue.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 12
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 12: Pola de Laviana - Alto de I'Angliru (108.5km)'. The 12th stage is bound to bring spectacle. At 108.5 km, the route takes in four intermediate climbs to finish uphill atop the iconic Angliru.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 13
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 13: Muros - Mirador de Ezaro (33.5km)'. This stage is perfect for time trialists with puncher's legs. After 31.9 km on the flat, the end climb kicks in. The Mirador de Ézaro is a monster of 1.8 km.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 14
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 14: Lugo - Ourense (205.8km)'. La Vuelta serves a demanding race through the Galician interior on stage 14. At 205.8 kilometres, the route travels from Lugo to Orense.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 15
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 15: Mos - Puebla de Sanabria (234.6km)'. At 234.6 km, the 15th stage is the longest race of this edition with hardly a flat metre. The finish lies 17 km after the last summit.

programme.title: La Vuelta a Espana HL '20: Stage 16
programme.desc: 'La Vuelta a Espana Highlights - Stage 16: Salamanca - Ciudad Rodrigo (162km)'. At 162 km the 16th stage travels from Salamanca to Ciudad Rodrigo. A demanding route with most elevation in the middle section is likely to favour attackers.
